Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing his probation having been revoked effective 10-06-16.   
Count 1 - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of four (4) years.   Two (2) years initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision, consecutive to 14 CF 526.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling and work towards his high school diploma, GED or HSED;
2) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
3) AODA assessment and follow through; 
4) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
8) No contact with any victim unless approved by the agent, except contact with Todd Ward as allowed;
9) No contact with any of the co-defendants.  
Defendant is given credit for 120 days already served.   
Court finds the defendan tis eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for the Substance Abuse Program.  
Count 5 - Defendant is sentenced to nine (9) months jail concurrent with count 1, but consecutive to 14 CF 526.   
